item.title: [CXF-5061] Invalid WSDL generated for List of Complex Type
item.description:
We are using CXF to do Code First development of both SOAP and REST web services. Here is our interface for the web service:

@Path("/test")
@Produces(BaseMediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
@Consumes(BaseMediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
@WebService(name = "TestService",
		portName = "TestServicePort",
		serviceName = "TestService",
		targetNamespace = "http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/test")
@SOAPBinding(parameterStyle = SOAPBinding.ParameterStyle.BARE)
public interface TestService
{
	@Path("/list")
	@GET
	@Produces(BaseMediaType.MULTIPART_RELATED)
	@WebMethod(operationName = "getList")
	public List<WrapperString> getList();
}

Whenever CXF creates the WSDL for the implementing class, the WSDL is invalid. Here is the WSDL that is created:

<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?><wsdl:definitions xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:wsdl="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/" xmlns:tns="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/test" xmlns:soap="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/wsdl/soap/" xmlns:ns1="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/http" name="TestService" targetNamespace="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/test">
  <wsdl:types>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:ns0="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/base" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/base">
  <xsd:complexType name="wrapperStringArray">
    <xsd:sequence>
      <xsd:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="item" nillable="true" type="ns0:WrapperString"/>
    </xsd:sequence>
  </xsd:complexType>
  <xsd:complexType name="WrapperString">
    <xsd:sequence>
      <xsd:element minOccurs="0" name="value" type="xsd:string"/>
    </xsd:sequence>
  </xsd:complexType>
  <xsd:element name="wrapperString" type="ns0:WrapperString"/>
</xsd:schema>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:tns="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/test" xmlns:ns0="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/base" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/test">
  <xsd:import namespace="http://enterprise.ltcourttech.com/services/base"/>
  <xsd:element name="getListResponse" nillable="true" type="ns0:WrapperStringArray"/>
</xsd:schema>
  </wsdl:types>
  <wsdl:message name="getListResponse">
    <wsdl:part element="tns:getListResponse" name="getListResponse">
    </wsdl:part>
  </wsdl:message>
  <wsdl:message name="getList">
  </wsdl:message>
  <wsdl:portType name="TestService">
    <wsdl:operation name="getList">
      <wsdl:input message="tns:getList" name="getList">
    </wsdl:input>
      <wsdl:output message="tns:getListResponse" name="getListResponse">
    </wsdl:output>
    </wsdl:operation>
  </wsdl:portType>
  <wsdl:binding name="TestServiceSoapBinding" type="tns:TestService">
    <soap:binding style="document" transport="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/http"/>
    <wsdl:operation name="getList">
      <soap:operation soapAction="" style="document"/>
      <wsdl:input name="getList">
        <soap:body use="literal"/>
      </wsdl:input>
      <wsdl:output name="getListResponse">
        <soap:body use="literal"/>
      </wsdl:output>
    </wsdl:operation>
  </wsdl:binding>
  <wsdl:service name="TestService">
    <wsdl:port binding="tns:TestServiceSoapBinding" name="TestServicePort">
      <soap:address location="http://mtefile/services/soap/test"/>
    </wsdl:port>
  </wsdl:service>
</wsdl:definitions>

Notice that the complexType is named "wrapperStringArray" yet the getListResponse is trying to use the type of "ns0:WrapperStringArray". The bug is that the case of the types does not match. I think the getListResponse type should be a lowercase "w". I ran another test with a List<String> and the types were correctly generated to "stringArray". It seems like CXF is messing the capitalization of the type when using complex objects. This is quite a high priority issue so we can get SOAP services to work correctly with a valid WSDL.
item.summary: Invalid WSDL generated for List of Complex Type

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

I can't reproduce this error anyway, could you please append a full testcase?
Like what's your WrapperString class looks like?

And do you still run into this issue if you remove restful related annotations?

Thanks

Freeman

Freeman, thanks for the response. I think have attached all of the files to recreate the problem. The TestService interface only has SOAP annotations. I have included the WrapperString JAXB annotated class, a default implementation of the service, and the spring configuration file for the service. Also, I have included the WSDL that is generated from CXF.

Hi Joshua,

I can't reproduce this error anyway with the files you attached here.

I will append the wsdl which generated from the testcase you append here.

Freeman
The wsdl generated from the testcase here

Hi Joshua,

I just commit a runnable testcase[1] which demonstrate how the valid wsdl get generated for list of complex type, basically it's based on the testcase you attached here.

You may wanna take a look to see how it works, and probably can tell the difference with your scenario.

[1]http://svn.apache.org/r1493644

Freeman

Freeman, do you think it could also be a namespace issue? I am using two namespaces instead of using the single target namespace, like you are in your example. In my example I am using two different namespaces, one for the WrapperString object and one for the service interface/class, and setting the schemas to qualify the namespace for the elements. Could you take a look at the namespaces in my example and modify your test case to match?

I'm using a package-info.java class to set the namespace and the FormDefault values for the WrapperString class. I've attached the file to the issue so that you can see how the namespace gets set differently for the WrapperString object than the TestService interface.

Joshua,

No, the package-info isn't the problem, take a look at my new commit with package-info.java[1], with this commit, the schema in the wsdl is like

<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:tns="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws/base" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws/base" version="1.0">
<xs:element name="wrapperString" type="tns:WrapperString"/>
<xs:complexType name="WrapperString">
<xs:sequence>
<xs:element minOccurs="0" name="value" type="xs:string"/>
</xs:sequence>
</xs:complexType>
<xs:complexType final="#all" name="WrapperStringArray">
<xs:sequence>
<xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0" name="item" nillable="true" type="tns:WrapperString"/>
</xs:sequence>
</xs:complexType>
</xs:schema>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:tns="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws" xmlns:ns0="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws/base" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" elementFormDefault="qualified" targetNamespace="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws">
<xsd:import namespace="http://cxf.apache.org/systest/jaxws/base"/>
<xsd:element name="getListResponse" nillable="true" type="ns0:WrapperStringArray"/>
</xsd:schema>

It's correct wsdl.

So you didn't append all your files here, right? My gut feeling is that you have ObjectFactory.java and WrapperStringArray.java where you have annotation like

@XmlType(name = "wrapperStringArray")

which explicitly specify the type name start from lower "w"

Anyway, if you can append a runnable testcase, it should be more helpful.

[1]http://svn.apache.org/r1493983

Freeman

Nope. I don't have any other files to commit. I don't have an ObjectFactory or WrapperStringArray class. "wrapperStringArray" (with the lower-case "w") is generated by CXF because the service is returning the List<WrapperString>. I really don't know what else could be causing the difference between between my test case and that one you wrote.
What would you need for a runnable test case? I provided all the source code files that I used to generate the CXF Soap Service.

You deploy the cxf endpoint as a war into tomcat, right?
Do you have other version of jaxws|jaxb api|impl in tomcat lib folder?

Could you append the project which you build the war, so that I can build the war from it and take a close look what's going on there.

No, sorry, Freeman. Our application is gigantic so I'm not going to be able to upload the project for you to build it yourself. It looks like jaxb-api-2.2.7 and jaxb-impl-2.2.6 are the jaxb jars on the classpath.

With CXF 2.7.5, you should have
WEB-INF/lib/jaxb-api-2.2.6.jar
WEB-INF/lib/jaxb-impl-2.2.6.jar
in the war.
But you have jaxb-api-2.2.7 and jaxb-impl-2.2.6, this mismatch may cause the error you encounter.

Anyway, if you can narrow down your project and provide the war project we can reproduce the error, it would be more helpful here.

I did make the changes to have version 2.2.6 of both the jaxb-api and the jaxb-impl libraries but that didn't make a difference. I am not able to slim down our applications. It would take me days of effort to be able to create a deployable project that I would be able to upload.
